Project Overview

This project is a Smart Construction Dashboard designed for personal use by construction professionals. It is tailored to manage construction project expenses, track stage-wise spending, and provide predictive insights for budget management. The dashboard enables users to input project details and receive automated predictions and analysis for ongoing construction work.

Purpose

The main purpose of the project is to help an individual contractor or construction manager:

Track the expenses for each construction stage.

Predict the expected cost for each stage.

Monitor whether the spending is within budget or over/under budget.

Make informed decisions on future stages and materials.

Models Used

Classification Model: Predicts the risk or spending status for each stage as Safe, Moderate, or High.

Model: Random Forest Classifier

Features: Project size, total project budget, encoded stage, total stage cost, expected stage cost

Output: Risk label indicating whether current spending is within expected range.

Regression Model: Predicts the expected cost for each stage.

Model: Random Forest Regressor

Features: Project size, total project budget, encoded stage

Output: Expected stage cost, which helps compare actual spending to predicted spending.

Dataset

The dataset includes details from 64,000 rows of construction projects with the following features:

Project ID

Project Size (sqft)

Total Project Budget

Stage Name

Stage Encoded

Total Stage Cost

Expected Stage Cost

Risk Label (Safe, Moderate, High)

The dataset is realistic and designed to simulate a variety of construction project scenarios.

Processing Flow

Load dataset and check for missing values.

Encode categorical features (stage names, risk labels).

Split data into training and testing sets.

Train Classification and Regression models.

Evaluate models using metrics (accuracy, MAE, MSE, R2 Score, classification report).

Save models for future use in applications.

Generate visualizations such as feature importance and confusion matrix for insights.

Integration with Personal Construction App

The trained models are embedded in a personal application to allow real-time predictions.

Users can input project details such as stage, amount spent, and project size.

The dashboard processes the input, predicts expected costs, and classifies the spending risk.

Provides actionable insights: whether the current spending is on track, overspending, or under budget.

This helps in planning materials, labor, and other expenses effectively.

Output

Stage-wise expected cost vs actual spending.

Risk label for each stage (Safe, Moderate, High).

Graphical visualizations of feature importance, cost deviation, and budget allocation.

Recommendations for budget adjustments in upcoming stages.

Benefits

Simplifies construction project expense tracking.

Provides predictive insights for budget optimization.

Helps prevent cost overruns and project delays.

Tailored for personal use, making it highly adaptable for individual contractors.

